 announed the event for levels 1-4 to come and fight Wac- all at once.  Whoever got the kill was rewarded.<br>
<br>
Funny- it should have been fun.  But invariably we got greedy people who wanted more stuff, or high levels who would come to the arena and blast the level 2's to oblivion, or people who had never heard of or participated in the event shouting that we were lying and only wanted to kill the low levels.<br>
<br>
Um.... yeah- I get my rocks off (ok- if I had rocks) by annihilating level three people. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One I always though would be fun was a /loc race.  But I never got to do it.  The way I wanted to do it was to get 9 friends together, and give them each a few stacks of something- each different from the rest.  Person #1 would get a few stacks of bone chips- #2 some metal bits, #3 short ales, etc.  Then, they would all go off somewhere in the zone (like N. Ro) and stand- sending me their loc.  I would designate each person a number.  I would tell the newbies the /loc of person #1 and off they would go.  When they found person #1, they would recieve one of the items in the stack to prove they had actually visited the loc.  Then they would be given the loc to person #2 and so on.  <br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
Problem is, there are few true newbies anymore, and no one else is interested in these events.<br>
<br>
Norrath just isn't as much fun as it used to be.  It's all uber uber uber. <p><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/thelizards/laur2.jpg><br>
